<subSubSection pageId="223" pageNumber="224" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="223.[151,1437,618,1723]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1374,1399]" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">Remarks.</emphasis>
This new species differs from 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1964" box="[686,817,1375,1398]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[686,817,1375,1398]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">A. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by having the body surface strongly 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[1263,1386,1374,1399]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; the antenna not elongate; the clypeus with the apical margin rounded; the antennal scrobe carinate; the notaulus narrow; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture fused with the first metapostnotal carina; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea and mesopleural suture closed; the paramere club-shaped; the basivolsella with inner margin apically excavated and with a short projection; the cuspis with the arms very short; and the aedeagus with the apical portion wide, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1964" box="[327,458,1555,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="venustus">
<emphasis box="[327,458,1555,1579]" italics="true" pageId="223" pageNumber="224">A. venustus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the body surface 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Kieffer" authorityYear="1908" box="[723,847,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="223" pageNumber="224" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="coriaceous">coriaceous</taxonomicName>
; the antenna elongate; the clypeus with the apical margin angulate; the antennal scrobe carinate, but weak; the notaulus very narrow; the metapostnotal-propodeal suture straight; the mesopleuron with the lower fovea and mesopleural suture opened; the paramere rounded; the basivolsella with a projection at the basal portion of the inner margin; the cuspis with the arms long; and the aedeagus with the apical portion slender.
</paragraph>
